Class ClusRuleSet

java.lang.Object
si.ijs.kt.clus.algo.rules.ClusRuleSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, ClusModel
public class ClusRuleSet extends Object implements ClusModel, Serializable
Class representing a set of predictive clustering rules.

      public void convertToPlainLinearTerms()

    • giveFormForWeightOptimization

      public OptimizationProblem.OptimizationParameter giveFormForWeightOptimization(PrintWriter outLogFile, RowData data) throws ClusException
      Returns the form of this rule set that can be used for weight optimization. The predictions should be always a value or NaN. NaN occurs if the rule does not cover the example OR the linear term predicts undefined attribute.
      Parameters:
      outLogFile - File stream for outputs.
      data - Data the optimization is based on.
      Returns:
      Parameters for optimization. Include true values and predictions for each of the data instances.
      Throws:
      ClusException

    • addRuleSet

      public int addRuleSet(ClusRuleSet newRules)
      Add rules in the given set to this rule set. Uniqueness is not checked because it is based on the test only. Thus different predictions for rules do not make rules different.
      Parameters:
      newRules - Rules to be added.
      Returns:
      How many added rules were unique when only descriptions are considered.

    • addRuleSet

      public int addRuleSet(ClusRuleSet newRules, boolean addOnlyUnique)
      Add rules in the given set to this rule set. Uniqueness is not checked because it is based on the test only. Thus different predictions for rules do not make rules different.
      Parameters:
      newRules - Rules to be added.
      addOnlyUnique - Add only unique rules?
      Returns:
      How many added rules were added when only descriptions are considered.

    • addDefaultRuleToRuleSet

      public double[] addDefaultRuleToRuleSet()
      For optimization, we need to make the default rule a real rule. We need a weight for it etc. This rule is the rule that covers all the examples (no test statement). Also if set in settings, remove the default prediction from other rules. return Default prediction. This may be removed from other base predictors.

    • addImplicitLinearTermsExplicitly

      public void addImplicitLinearTermsExplicitly(ArrayList<Double> weights, int indFirstLinTerm)
      If used implicit linear term usage, add the linear terms with great enough weight.
      Parameters:
      weights - Optimized weights.
      indFirstLinTerm - Index of first linear term.
